  "texts": [
    "8 provides an SEM photo highlighting the influence of GGBFS on the concrete microstructure.",
    "MKMK enhances concrete microstructure by facilitating the pozzolanic reaction, which generates additional calcium silicate hydrate (C-S-H) gel, essential for concrete's strength and durability.",
    "Singh and Murugan [73] found that MK improves energy absorption and crack resistance by densifying the microstructure and reducing pore sizes.",
    "Jiang et al. [72] noted that it reduces porosity and improves the interfacial transition zone (ITZ) between cement paste and aggregates, increasing bond strength and minimizing harmful substance infiltration.",
    "Zhan et al. [74] observed that MK decreases the formation of less durable calcium hydroxide, promotes a finer pore structure, and enhances resistance to chloride penetration."
  ],
